---
import { snapshot } from "../../roadmap-data";
---

<section class="section-border reveal bg-bg-subtle">
  <div class="wrap py-10 sm:py-12">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-6 text-center">Where we are today</p>
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-4xl grid-cols-2 gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-md border border-border bg-border md:grid-cols-4">
      {
        snapshot.map((s) => (
          <div class="bg-bg px-5 py-8 text-center">
            <div class="whitespace-nowrap text-[1.5rem] font-semibold tracking-tight">{s.value}</div>
            <div class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-text-muted">{s.label}</div>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
    <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-[68ch] text-center text-sm text-text-faint">
      Published on npm; the site you're reading is the docs. The framework runs
      on macOS, Linux and Windows (x64), the pinned-engine store and CLI are in
      place, and self-contained relocatable WebKits - including a from-source
      WinCairo build - load from the store in CI. The per-method truth lives on
      the <a href="/docs/migrating/parity" class="text-accent-text underline underline-offset-2">parity page</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
